com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.interfaces

Interface Factory<F,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    F - The Type of the Object, required to create the T
    T - The Type of the Object, which is instantiated by calling the create(Object) method
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Factory<F,T>
    A Factory interface is used to create any Object.

    In contrast to the SimpleFactory, this interface expects a parameter inside of the create(Object) method. This might be used to create the Object. It either is the base or a parameter of the newly created Object

    In contrast to the Adapter interface, the call of the create(Object) method will ALWAYS create a new Instance of the said type T.

    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T create(F f)
      By calling this method, this Class instantiates (creates) the new Object.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        T create(F f)
        By calling this method, this Class instantiates (creates) the new Object. It should NOT return any previously created instance, but a new instance every time the Method is called.
        Parameters:
        f - the Object, required to create the object, which this factory should create.
        Returns:
        a new Instance of the defined Type.
